@vanzin which beeline/hive version are you using? Using the client from the client module or a beeline using Apache Hive 3.0 should work.

Yes the tests are UTs rather than ITs, since the client and the server run in the same JVM. But actually the Spark sessions are executed as they would be in a IT, so I think the problem here could be detected only running on a (mini-)cluster (probably doing something like what was removed in LIVY-473).

Anyway LIVY-502 is ready at the PR: https://github.com/apache/incubator-livy/pull/117. If you have time we can go ahead with its review.

@vanzin thanks for your review, I have corrected them one by one in recent commit. But continuous-integration failed because of Spark 2.4 ITs. I have no idea how to fix it, have you met this before?

